PRESIDENT John Magufuli has reiterated a call upon followers of all religions to embrace spirit of unity and live as per teachings of Holly Books. “By doing this you will not only live life that pleases God but will also help building the country,” the President stated when graced the 20th Quran competition today in Dar es Salaam. The competition, which is organized by the Al-Hikma Foundation, has this year attracted participants from 18 African countries. This is the first time for President Magufuli attending the Quran Recitation Contest, implementing his last year’s promise that he will attend.